nguage shift from Gorani to Kurdish in the region. The book offers insights into contact-induced change in social contexts in which a language is maintained as a demarcation of communal identity in a multilingual setting.  aIssued also in print.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aThis eBook is made available Open Access under a CC BY-NC-ND 4.0 license: uhttps://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-nd/4.0  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 02. Jun 2024) 4aBedrohte Sprachen. 4aGorani. 4aKurdisch. 4aNeo-Armamaic. 4aPersisch. 4aSprachkontakt. 7aLANGUAGE ARTS & DISCIPLINES / Linguistics / General.2bisacsh  aGorani.  aKurdish.  aLanguage Contact.  aLanguage Endangerment.  aNeo-Aramaic.  aPersian.1 aMohammadirad, Masoud , eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDe Gruyter Mouton eBook Package 2024z978311143804708iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2023 Englishz978311131929208iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2023z9783111318912oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Linguistics 2023 Englishz978311131916208iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Linguistics 2023z9783111318240oZDB-23-DSP0 cEPUBz97831112100700 cprintz978311120578640uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9783111209180zOpen Access7040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783111209180zOpen Access70423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9783111209180/original  a978-3-11-131916-2 EBOOK PACKAGE Linguistics 2023 Englishb2023  a978-3-11-131929-2 EBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2023 Englishb2023  a978-3-11-143804-7 De Gruyter Mouton eBook Package 2024b2024  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-DGGb2023  aZDB-23-DSPb2023  aZDB-23-GOA